Package: nstdFileRd
Type: Package
Title: Reads Data Files in Nested Folder Structure
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Pranav", "Sachdev", email = "sachdevpranav1@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Pranav Sachdev <sachdevpranav1@gmail.com>
Description: 
     Read data files residing within the nested folder structure.
     Provide the path of the root directory and all the csv and excel data files in the nested folder structure gets loaded.
     1. The naming convention of the read files will be: 
        a. For CSV - ProjData_<FolderName1>_<FolderName2>_<FolderName3>._filename
        b.For XLSX/XLS -	ProjData_<FolderName1>_<FolderName2>_<FolderName3>._filename_SheetName1
   	2. A report of unread files (maybe due to corrupt data) will be generated in the end in a dataframe named 'err_list'.
Depends: R (>= 2.15.0)
Imports: 
    readxl,
    stringr,
    utils
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
